annotationA: Succinate dehydrogenase, subunit C, isoform A; Succinate dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) activity; succinate dehydrogenase activity; electron carrier activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: response to oxidative stress; succinate metabolic process; determination of adult lifespan; mitochondrial electron transport, succinate to ubiquinone; tricarboxylic acid cycle
annotationB: ATP synthase subunit gamma, mitochondrial; Mitochondrial membrane ATP synthase (F(1)F(0) ATP synthase or Complex V) produces ATP from ADP in the presence of a proton gradient across the membrane which is generated by electron transport complexes of the respiratory chain. F-type ATPases consist of two structural domains, F(1) - containing the extramembraneous catalytic core, and F(0) - containing the membrane proton channel, linked together by a central stalk and a peripheral stalk.
